S.B. NO. --
1 (b) Beginning on July 1, [2026,] 2028, the board shall
2 issue a certification to an applicant or law enforcement officer
3 who meets the requirements of subsection (a) or who has
4 satisfactorily completed a program or course of instruction in
5 another jurisdiction that the board deems to be equivalent in
6 content and quality to the requirements of subsection (a)."
7 SECTION 2. Section 139-7, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
8 amended by amending subsection (a) to read as follows:
9 "(a) No person shall be appointed or employed as a law
10 enforcement officer by any county police department, the
11 department of law enforcement, the department of land and
12 natural resources, the department of taxation, or the department
13 of the attorney general after June 30, [2026,] 2028, unless the
14 person possesses a valid certification issued by the board
15 pursuant to section 139-6(b)."
16 SECTION 3. Statutory material to be repealed is bracketed
17 and stricken. New statutory material is underscored.
18 SECTION 4. This Act shall take effect upon its approval.
